                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13656702" author="dagw" created="Tue, 14 May 2013 05:17:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Uploading a patch to remove the unused permission in both the policy files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It also formats the comments consistently, removes trailing blanks and breaks too long lines.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running regressions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13657043" author="chaase3" created="Tue, 14 May 2013 14:12:16 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The template.policy looks great, Dag &amp;#8211; +1. I did not look as closely at the server.policy (the one that is not in the docs), since I am not sure what its contents should be, but it looks good too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are a few differences in line breaks between this patch and the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6160&quot; title=&quot;Fixes needed to documentation topics on security policy permissions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-6160&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-6160&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; one &amp;#8211; those don&apos;t matter, I think. (They are lines that I shortened to make the content fit in the PDF, which has narrow margins.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, I think I will reopen &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6160&quot; title=&quot;Fixes needed to documentation topics on security policy permissions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-6160&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-6160&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to fix a few formatting inconsistencies in comment characters and also to remove the clause about Java SE 5, since that will be obsolete soon anyway and it saves us another piece of cleanup later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13659315" author="dagw" created="Thu, 16 May 2013 08:05:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Kim. I&apos;ll commit it then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13659330" author="dagw" created="Thu, 16 May 2013 08:20:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Comitted svn 1483215, resolving.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13739827" author="mamtas" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 17:19:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Dag, this jira is on the list of backport to 10.8. Is it ok to backport? thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13785042" author="dagw" created="Thu, 3 Oct 2013 13:38:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t see that string (jvmInstanceId) in any source files except policy files in the 10.8 code base, so I believe the answer is yes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13913297" author="mikem" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 18:44:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;consider for 10.10 backport&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13913759" author="mikem" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 23:50:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this looks like a change that applies to newer jvm&apos;s, but may not apply to jvm&apos;s supported in previous releases so marking as not appropriate for backport.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
